children.name: catalog
children.description:
Root container of yang-catalog holding two main branches -
modules and vendors. The modules sub-tree contains all the modules in
the catalog and all of their metadata with their implementations.
The vendor sub-tree holds modules for specific vendors, platforms,
software-versions, and software-flavors. It contains reference to a
name and revision of the module in order to reference the module's full
set of metadata.

children.name: modules
children.description: Container holding the list of modules

children.name: module
children.description: Each entry represents one revision of one module\nfor one organization.

children.name: name
children.description: The YANG module or submodule name.

children.name: revision
children.description: The YANG module or submodule revision date.\nA zero-length string is used if no revision statement\nis present in the YANG module or submodule.

children.name: organization
children.description:
This statement defines the party responsible for this
module.  The argument is a string that is used to specify a textual
description of the organization(s) under whose auspices this module
was developed.

children.name: ietf
children.description: Include this container for the IETF-specific organization metadata.

children.name: ietf-wg
children.description: Working group that authored the document containing this module.

children.name: namespace
children.description: The XML namespace identifier for this module.

children.name: schema
children.description:
Contains a URL that represents the YANG schema
resource for this module or submodule.
This leaf will only be present if there is a URL
available for retrieval of the schema for this entry.

children.name: generated-from
children.description: This statement defines weather the module was generated or not.\nDefault value is set to not-applicable, which means that module\nwas created manualy and not generated.

children.name: maturity-level
children.description: The current maturity of the module with respect to the body that created it.\nThis allows one to understand where the module is in its overall life cycle.

children.name: document-name
children.description: The name of the document from which the module was extracted or taken;\nor that provides additional context about the module.

children.name: author-email
children.description: Contact email of the author who is responsible for this module.

children.name: reference
children.description: A string that is used to specify a textual cross-reference to an external document, either\nanother module that defines related management information, or a document that provides\nadditional information relevant to this definition.

children.name: module-classification
children.description: The high-level classification of the given YANG module.

children.name: compilation-status
children.description: Status of the module, whether it was possible to compile this YANG module or\nthere are still some errors/warnings.

children.name: compilation-result
children.description: Link to the result of the compilation explaining specifically what error or\nwarning occurred.  This is not existing if compilation status is PASSED.

children.name: prefix
children.description:
Statement of yang that is used to define the prefix associated with
the module and its namespace. The prefix statement's argument is
the prefix string that is used as a prefix to access a module. The
prefix string MAY be used to refer to definitions contained in the
module, e.g., if:ifName.

children.name: yang-version
children.description: The optional yang-version statement specifies which version of the\nYANG language was used in developing the module.

children.name: description
children.description:
This statement takes as an argument a string that
contains a human-readable textual description of this definition.
The text is provided in a language (or languages) chosen by the
module developer; for the sake of interoperability, it is RECOMMENDED
to choose a language that is widely understood among the community of
network administrators who will use the module.

children.name: contact
children.description:
This statement provides contact information for the module.
The argument is a string that is used to specify contact information
for the person or persons to whom technical queries concerning this
module should be sent, such as their name, postal address, telephone
number, and electronic mail address.

children.name: module-type
children.description: Whether a file contains a YANG module or sub-module.

children.name: belongs-to
children.description: Name of the module that includes this submodule.

children.name: tree-type
children.description: The type of data element tree used by the module as it relates to the\nNetwork Management Datastores Architecture.

children.name: yang-tree
children.description: This leaf provides a URI that points to the ASCII tree format of the module in\ndraft-ietf-netmod-yang-tree-diagrams format.

children.name: expires
children.description: Date and time of when this module expires (if it expires).  This will typically be used for\nmodules that have not been fully ratified.

children.name: expired
children.description: Whether or not this module has expired.  If the current date is beyond the expires date, then expired\nshould be true.

children.name: submodule
children.description: Each entry represents one submodule within the\nparent module.

children.name: name
children.description: The YANG module or submodule name.

children.name: revision
children.description: The YANG module or submodule revision date.\nA zero-length string is used if no revision statement\nis present in the YANG module or submodule.

children.name: schema
children.description:
Contains a URL that represents the YANG schema
resource for this module or submodule.
This leaf will only be present if there is a URL
available for retrieval of the schema for this entry.

children.name: dependencies
children.description: Each entry represents one dependency.

children.name: name
children.description: The YANG module or submodule name.

children.name: revision
children.description: The YANG module or submodule revision date.\nA zero-length string is used if no revision statement\nis present in the YANG module or submodule.

children.name: schema
children.description:
Contains a URL that represents the YANG schema
resource for this module or submodule.
This leaf will only be present if there is a URL
available for retrieval of the schema for this entry.

children.name: dependents
children.description: Each entry represents one dependent.

children.name: name
children.description: The YANG module or submodule name.

children.name: revision
children.description: The YANG module or submodule revision date.\nA zero-length string is used if no revision statement\nis present in the YANG module or submodule.

children.name: schema
children.description:
Contains a URL that represents the YANG schema
resource for this module or submodule.
This leaf will only be present if there is a URL
available for retrieval of the schema for this entry.

children.name: semantic-version
children.description: The formal semantic version of a module as provided by the module\nitself.  If the module does not provide a semantic version, this leaf\nwill not be specified.

children.name: derived-semantic-version
children.description:
The semantic version of a module as compared to other revisions of
the same module.  This value is computed algorithmically by ordering
all revisions of a given module and comparing them to look for backwards
incompatible changes.

children.name: implementations
children.description: Container holding lists of per-module implementation details.

children.name: implementation
children.description: List of module implementations.

children.name: vendor
children.description: Organization that implements this module.

children.name: platform
children.description: Platform on which this module is implemented.

children.name: software-version
children.description:
Name of the version of software.  With respect to most network device appliances,
this will be the operating system version.  But for other YANG module
implementation, this would be a version of appliance software.  Ultimately,
this should correspond to a version string that will be recognizable by
the consumers of the platform.

children.name: software-flavor
children.description: A variation of a specific version where\nYANG model support may be different.  Depending on the vendor, this could\nbe a license, additional software component, or a feature set.

children.name: os-version
children.description: Version of the operating system using this module.  This is primarily useful if\nthe software implementing the module is an application that requires a specific\noperating system.

children.name: feature-set
children.description: An optional feature of the software that is required in order to implement this\nmodule.  Some form of this must be incorporated in software-version or\nsoftware-flavor, but can be broken out here for additional clarity.

children.name: os-type
children.description: Type of the operating system using this module.  This is primarily useful if\nthe software implementing the module is an application that requires a\nspecific operating system.

children.name: feature
children.description: List of YANG feature names from this module that are\nsupported by the server, regardless of whether they are\ndefined in the module or any included submodule.

children.name: deviation
children.description:
List of YANG deviation module names and revisions
used by this server to modify the conformance of
the module associated with this entry.  Note that
the same module can be used for deviations for
multiple modules, so the same entry MAY appear
within multiple 'module' entries.
The deviation module MUST be present in the 'module'
list, with the same name and revision values.
The 'conformance-type' value will be 'implement' for
the deviation module.

children.name: name
children.description: The YANG module or submodule name.

children.name: revision
children.description: The YANG module or submodule revision date.\nA zero-length string is used if no revision statement\nis present in the YANG module or submodule.

children.name: conformance-type
children.description: Indicates the type of conformance the server is claiming\nfor the YANG module identified by this entry.

children.name: vendors
children.description: Container holding lists of organizations that publish YANG modules.

children.name: vendor
children.description: List of organizations publishing YANG modules.

children.name: name
children.description:
Name of the maintaining organization -- the name should be
supplied in the official format used by the organization.
Standards Body examples:
  IETF, IEEE, MEF, ONF, etc.
Commercial entity examples:
  AT&T, Facebook, <Vendor>
Name of industry forum examples:
OpenConfig, OpenDaylight, ON.Lab

children.name: name
children.description: Name of the platform

children.name: protocols
children.description: List of the protocols

children.name: protocol
children.description: YANG-based protocol that is used on the device.  New identities\nare expected to be added to address other YANG-based protocols.

children.name: name
children.description: Identity of the YANG-based protocol that is supported.

children.name: protocol-version
children.description: Version of the specific protocol.

children.name: capabilities
children.description: Listed name of capabilities that are\nsupported by the specific device.
